#!/Users/donna-broker/venv/bin/python3
"""General, site-agnostic browser-goal executor.

# UNVERIFIED in CI — live Playwright/login only runs in the donna-broker
# browser env. Pure helpers are unit-tested.

Subprocess contract: reads JSON {capability, params} from stdin, credentials
from the DONNA_CREDS_FD pipe, writes JSON result to stdout.
Exit 0 = success/done/planned, exit 1 = failure {error_code, detail}.

Params schema:
  site           — profile key, e.g. "everyoneactive"
  goal           — plain-English goal string
  phase          — "plan" or "execute"
  max_price      — optional int (pence) for pricing gate
  commit_token   — optional str, live human-approved commit token
  plan_summary   — optional str, context from a prior plan phase

Security invariants enforced here:
  - Site credentials are read from the broker fd and stored only in the
    _PlaywrightBrowser adapter. They are NEVER passed to the model; the
    agent receives {{cred:username}} / {{cred:password}} placeholders
    which the adapter substitutes at execute time.
  - The network-layer route handler (context.route) enforces the
    allowlist from the site profile (invariant 5).
  - The gate (browser_gate.Gate) is the commit-token authority; the
    runner consults it before every action.
  - Secrets never enter the ledger (browser_ledger.Ledger scrubs
    credential placeholders before writing).

Design: docs/superpowers/specs/browser-goal-agent-plan2.md
Spec: security-v1.1 §8 (capability executor), §17 (Phase 2 browser executor).
"""
